nk\": 0.0016240507812295413, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Court for Arbitration of Sport dismissed Thomas' request for arbitration with World Aquatics, according to a ruling released Wednesday.\", \"from\": 751, \"to\": 890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999997703526, \"rank\": 1.8840443921802597e-10, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The governing body in swimming made its ruling in 2022, which essentially banned transgender swimmers from competing in female events.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"World Aquatics also created an \\\"open\\\" category for transgender athletes.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas asked the Switzerland-based court to overturn the rules, saying they were invalid, unlawful and discriminatory.\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1100, \"end\": 1106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999997703526, \"rank\": 1.8840443921802597e-10, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The panel concludes that she lacks standing to challenge the policy and the operational requirements in the framework of the present proceeding,\\\" the court said in a ruling.\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The three-judge panel said USA Swimming had no authority to \\\"to modify such scope of application\\\" of its rules.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1507, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1423, \"end\": 1435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USA Swimming\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Swimming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lia Thomas, a transgender UPenn swimmer who competed for two full seasons as a man before 'transitioning' into a female, shattered women's records in Akron, Ohio in 2021.\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1509, \"end\": 1519, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lia_Thomas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lia Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lia_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lia_Thomas\"}, {\"begin\": 1535, \"end\": 1540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Pennsylvania\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UPenn\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Pennsylvania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Pennsylvania\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\", \"score\": 0.9996549840630334, \"rank\": 0.00024387616133882692, \"text\": \"Ohio\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thomas also finished one of the races 38 seconds ahead of the woman who finished in second place.\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1681, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.9999999997703526, \"rank\": 1.8840443921802597e-10, \"text\": \"Th